author: peters_world_of_flags
stickers:
next up, we have the flag of Israel. this flag is white, with a central 6-pointed star of David in blue. at the top and bottom are two thin blue horizontal stripes. this flag originated as a zionist symbol in 1891. this flag was adopted as the national flag of Israel shortly after its independence in 1948. the blue stripes on the flag are meant to reflect the tallit, or the traditional Jewish prayer shawls. the 6-pointed star of David is a very old symbol, however throughout history it was not exclusively used by Jewish people. it was only in the last 200 years or so that it became widely recognized as a Jewish symbol, hence its position on this flag. to fold the flag of Israel, it is first folded into thirds along the width. after this, the flag is folded into thirds along the height. this leaves the 6-pointed star of David on top. I folded it again off camera just to get it to a more manageable size. as usual, feel free to correct any mistakes.

author: nowthis
body: Residents on the streets of Tel Aviv are calling for Israel‚Äôs Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to step down. Netanyahu has already been facing backlash domestically in recent months prior to the outbreak of violence this past week that has seen hundreds of Israelis and Palestinians killed. This past summer, thousands of protesters marched into Jerusalem to protest the Netanyahu government‚Äôs plan for potential judicial overhaul, which would have stripped Israel‚Äôs Supreme Court of the ability to block government decisions that it deemed unreasonable. Others are frustrated at Netanyahu's decision earlier this year to advance the planning and promotion of more than 4,000 settlement units in the occupied West Bank. Per Reuters, most countries deem the building of settlements on this land illegal under international law, and warned that the move would risk escalating tensions between Israel and Palestine. There have also been reports this week in which Egyptian intelligence officials allege that Israel‚Äôs government had been warned about, but downplayed, the prospect of ‚Äòsomething big‚Äô happening prior to the start of Hamas‚Äô deadly attack on October 7. Netanyahu, however, has since denied that such a warning was ever issued. Several high-profile media publications, such as the Guardian and Israel-based Haaretz, have also called on Netanyahu to resign. #israel #telaviv #benjaminnetanyahu #palestine
